items.name: Benedikta Harman - Final Fantasy XVI (Character)
items.description:
This is a LORA of the character Benedikta Harman from FF16.

To prompt her enter "<lora:BenediktaHarman:strength>Benediktaharman, fur-trimmed coat". She is partially trained on her ingame appearances as well using the "realistic" tag, but also functions perfectly fine without it.

I highly suggest generating with this model using hi-res fix. The dataset used to make her was really small and specific due to the nature of her ingame appearances. This LORA is usually the best looking at 0.6 ~ 0.75 strength, and was trained on AnyLora at Clip Skip 2.

Expect a remake of this if more data becomes readily available.

items.name: [Concept] Stereogram (Cross-eyed) - generating stereoscopic images
items.description:
This Lora generates stereograms that can be viewed stereoscopically with cross-eyed viewing.

v2 released : Higher success rate than v1, more stable picture including background (I believe).

Trigger word: stereogram
Some Interesting keywords: pointing at viewer, reaching towards viewer, aiming at viewer

You may consider including keywords such as closed mouth, open mouth, parted lips, etc. to align the mouth expressions in the left and right images

More detailed prompt seems to stabilize the picture..

Suitable weights: 0.5 ~; seem to vary from model to model.
Try to find the best value starting with a small value.
It appears that higher weights do not necessarily result in more stable output.

Recommended resolutions: 768x512, 768x768, 768x384

Inpaint can be helpful in correcting minor mismatches between images (e.g., mouth expressions).

The yield is not very high. It is even more difficult with character Loras.
It may be better to use LoRA Block Weight and set other Lora to OUTALL or OUTD.

Please share your creative work!

items.name: X-RAY
items.description:
If you find our articles informative, please follow me to receive updates. It would be even better if you could also follow our ko-fi, where there are many more articles and tutorials that I believe would be very beneficial for you!

如果你觉得我们的文章有料，请关注我获得更新通知，
如果能同时关注我们的 ko-fi 就更好了，
那里有多得多的文章和教程! 相信能使您获益良多.

For collaboration and article reprint inquiries, please send an email to aigarlic@pm.me
合作和文章转载 请发送邮件至 aigarlic@pm.me

By: Ash0080

中文


我一直期待着能有一个真正的(其实也不是)x-ray模型，而不是裸体透视那种奇怪的东西。

但我等了几个月它也没有出现，因此我自己训练了它。

因为这是一个style模型，因此它有很强的泛化性，几乎能应用于任何模型，但我发现似乎它在2D的高对比度模型下无法得到想象中的效果，这是你需要注意的

我尝试许多模型，有一些不错的放在了预览图中，希望你们能够喜欢

Tips:

  1. 通常使用, 加入x-ray关键词触发，

  1. 大概有两种使用方法, 一种应用方式是可以配合skeleton, skull等实现类似真实的x-ray透视效果，第二种方法是只利用它对style的影响，实现一种风格化的效果

  2. 可以在各种不同类型的模型上尝试，但画girl并不拿手

  3. 无论哪种方式，它都会使图片倾向于单色调，这会导致你在hires时遇到困难，如果你画的是肖像，建议hires强度0.15-0.2， 如果是机械或局部透视，则可以在0.2-0.6之间尝试

已知的问题:

  1. 人体骨架结构并没有很清晰，尤其是盆骨，因为我并不是用真正的x-ray图片训练的，我打算在之后的版本中尝试加强这一点；

  2. 有些物体画不出透视，比如狗，因为我用的样本集非常小，这点也在之后补充；

  3. 对比度的问题，感觉当前版本的亮度有点高，希望在之后的版本中弱化一些；


日文（translated by GPT）

実際にはx-rayモデルがあればいいなとずっと待っていました。裸の透視図ではなく、本物のモデルが欲しかったのです。

しかし、何ヶ月も待っても出てこなかったので、自分で訓練しました。

これはスタイルモデルなので、汎用性が非常に高く、ほとんどのモデルに適用できますが、2Dの高コントラストモデルでは想像した効果が得られないことがあるようです。注意が必要です。

私はたくさんのモデルを試しましたが、いくつかはプレビュー画像に入れており、気に入っていただけると思います。

ヒント：

  1. 通常はx-rayキーワードを追加してトリガーします。

  2. 2つの使用方法があります。1つはスケルトン、スカルなどと組み合わせて、実際のx-ray視点を再現する方法です。2番目の方法は、スタイルに影響を与えるだけで、スタイル化された効果を実現する方法です。

  3. 様々な種類のモデルで試すことができますが、女の子を描くのは苦手です。

  4. どちらの方法でも、画像は単色傾向になります。これは、hires時に問題が発生する可能性があります。肖像画を描いている場合は、hires強度を0.15〜0.2に設定することをお勧めします。機械や局所的な透視を描いている場合は、0.2〜0.6の範囲で試すことができます。

既知の問題：

  1. 人体の骨格構造が明確ではなく、特に骨盤部分が不明瞭です。実際のx-ray画像を使用していないため、この点を強化するために今後のバージョンで試みる予定です。

  2. 犬など、一部の物体は透視を描くことができません。私が使用したサンプル集が非常に小さいため、この点を今後補完する予定です。

  3. コントラストの問題です。現在のバージョンの明るさが高すぎるように感じるため、今後のバージョンでこれを弱めることを希望しています。

English

I have been looking forward to a real (well, not really) x-ray model, rather than the strange kind of nude see-through glasses.

But after waiting for several months, it still didn't appear, so I trained it myself.

Because this is a style model, it has strong generalization ability and can be applied to almost any model. However, I found that it cannot achieve the desired effect on high-contrast 2D models, which is something to be aware of.

I tried many models and some of them are good and are shown in the preview images. I hope you will like them.

Tips:

  1. Add the keyword "x-ray" to trigger it.

  2. There are two main ways to use it. One is to combine it with skeleton, skull, etc. to achieve a realistic x-ray perspective, and the other is to use its effect on style to achieve a stylized effect.

  3. It can be tried on various types of models, but I'm not good at drawing girls.

  4. Regardless of the method, it tends to make the image monochromatic, which can make it difficult when working with hires. If you're drawing a portrait, I recommend setting the hires strength to 0.15-0.2. For mechanical or local perspective, you can try between 0.2-0.6.

Known issues:

  1. The skeletal structure of the human body is not very clear, especially the pelvis, because I did not use real x-ray images to train it. I plan to try to improve this in future versions.

  2. Some objects cannot be drawn with perspective, such as dogs, because the sample set I used is very small. I plan to supplement this in the future.

  3. There is an issue with contrast, as the current version's brightness is a bit high. I hope to weaken this in future versions.

items.name: Color Separation_B_1.1|差分|Differential|차이|
items.description:
Color separation with red preservation

My friend likes the way I edit her photos with this color adjustment. She wanted to have an "LORA" that could achieve the same effect on AI, so I created one. It mainly changes the overall color saturation by reducing blue and green while preserving red, along with some personal preferences adjustments. Negative values will increase the overall color of blue and green, while positive values will decrease them, resulting in desaturated images. It can be used for both real-life and anime-style images. If there are any visual distortions, please try adjusting the "LoRA Block Weight" or enlarging the image. Please use it in compliance with local laws, without harming others or engaging in illegal activities. If you have any ideas for improving this LORA, feel free to leave a comment.

色の分離、赤の保持

友人は私が彼女の写真をこのように調整するのが好きで、同じ効果をAI上で実現できる「LORA」を持ちたいと思っていました。そこで、それを作成しました。主に全体的な色彩飽和度を変え、青と緑を減らし、赤を保持します。また、個人の好みに合わせた調整も行います。負の値は青と緑の色彩を増加させ、正の値はそれらを減少させ、低彩度の画像を生成します。リアルな写真やアニメの画像に使用することができます。画面に損傷がある場合は、「LoRA Block Weight」を調整するか、画像を拡大してみてください。使用に際しては、地元の法律を遵守し、他人に害を与えたり違法行為を行わないようにしてください。このLORAの改善のアイデアがあれば、コメントをお寄せください。

색상 분리와 빨간색 보존

내 친구는 나가 그녀의 사진을 이렇게 편집하는 것을 좋아합니다. "AI"에서 동일한 효과를 얻을 수 있는 "LORA"를 소유하길 원해서 만들었습니다. 주로 전체적인 색상 포화도를 변경하고 파란색과 초록색을 감소시키면서 빨간색을 보존하며 개인적인 선호도에 맞게 조정합니다. 음수 값은 전체적인 색상의 파란색과 초록색을 증가시키고, 양수 값은 감소시켜 저포화도의 이미지를 생성합니다. 실사나 애니메이션 스타일의 이미지에 사용할 수 있습니다. 화면이 손상된 경우에는 "LoRA Block Weight"를 조정하거나 이미지를 확대해 보십시오. 사용 시 귀하의 지역 법률을 준수하고, 다른 사람을 해치거나 불법 활동을 하지 마십시오. 이 LORA에 대한 개선 아이디어가 있으면 댓글을 남겨주십시오.

色彩抽離保留紅

我的朋友喜歡我幫她照片這樣調色
希望能擁有一個能在"AI"上使用同樣效果的"LORA"所以製作了
主要是改變整體色彩飽和度降低藍色和綠色保留紅跟一些個人喜好的調整
負值會增加整體色彩藍色和綠色 正值會降低藍色和綠色產生低飽和度圖
可以在真實或者動漫類型中使用 使用如果有畫面破損,請嘗試“LoRA Block Weight”進行調整或者將圖片放大
使用請遵守你所在地區法律,不要傷害他人並且違法 如果對此LORA有改進的想法歡迎你留言

希望能拥有一个能在"AI"上使用同样效果的"LORA"所以制作了

modelVersions.name: Blue_1.1
modelVersions.description:
Due to the initial production without considering the addition of versions, the naming may be confusing, and I apologize for that. Positive values will decrease saturation in other colors and preserve blue, while negative values will decrease blue and increase saturation in other colors. Blue is not equivalent to cyan.

最初の制作時にはバージョンの追加を考慮していなかったため、命名が混乱を招く可能性があり、その点についてお詫び申し上げます。正の値は他の色の彩度を減少させ、青を保持しますが、負の値は青を減少させ、他の色の彩度を増加させます。青はシアンとは異なります

처음에 제작할 때 추가 버전을 고려하지 않았기 때문에 명명이 혼란스러울 수 있으며, 이에 대해 사과드립니다. 양수 값은 다른 색상의 채도를 감소시키고 파란색을 보존하며, 음수 값은 파란색을 감소시키고 다른 색상의 채도를 증가시킵니다. 파란색은 청록색과 같지 않습니다.

由于最初的制作没有考虑到添加版本，命名可能会让人感到困惑，对此我表示歉意。正值会降低其他颜色的饱和度，保留蓝色；负值则会降低蓝色并增加其他颜色的饱和度。蓝色并非等同于青色

由於一開始製作沒有想到會追加版本 所以取名可能讓人混亂 非常抱歉 正值 會降低其他飽和度 保留藍色 負值則會降低藍色增加其他色彩飽和度 藍色不等於青色

items.name: Slayer's NijiLike V5
items.description:
"It's about the journey, not the destination."

Heya, if you like my work, feel free to buy me a Ko-Fi! It is greatly appreciated, and it makes more of my work possible! <3

The first of the NijiLike series, NijiLike V5 LoRA is based on my own generations with Nijijourney. It is not related to any of the other Nijijourney/Midjourney generations I've seen out there, but the more Nijijourney styles we have, the better I suppose! NijiLike works best on anime models, this is tested well with MeinaMix!

This version of NijiLike is trained with 28 images, providing a direct, focused anime-like output, inspired by modern anime screencaps. The trigger word is xsv5_style, though it can probably work without it? For more controlled outputs, I recommend setting the weight to 0.4 to 0.6, though feel free to experiment to your liking!

Storytime:

It is my first LoRA to be developed, thanks to holostrawberry's LoRA generation tutorial, which helped me a lot here. As a side effect, while I did implement a global_activation_tag to it, it's mostly optional and it's just me trying to get around things. Sometimes people are bound to make mistakes.

I also do not have a good PC to develop faster images, so these things took quite a lot of time (around 1 - 4 minutes per image, sometimes even more) to even generate one image of this. But regardless, it is a community effort after all.

Hopefully, all of these images that I've generated will be put into good use. And there will be more NijiLike LoRA to come!

items.name: Beach Poses
items.description:
This is a new set of Beach type poses to the collection. This set contains a total of 42 different kind of beach poses, each pose has been captured from 25 different angles, giving you a wide range of options.

Please keep in mind that due to the more dynamic poses or camera angles, some images may need to be resized to fit your specific needs.

All the images in the set are in png format with the background removed, making it possible to use multiple images in a single scene without worrying about overlapping backgrounds. Additionally, the Controlnet system does not require a background to use the images, so they can be imported as they are.

If you want to be more safe on the image generation with poses, you can use any image editing software to add the black background on the back of the poses.

Some poses may be too far from the scene and require zooming in for stable diffusion to capture them properly.

Some poses in the set, such as those with extreme angles like top-down or bottom-right upward views, may be challenging for stable diffusion to comprehend without additional prompts support. If stable diffusion is unable to understand or generate these extreme poses, it is advisable to move on and try other poses.

In this set some poses can cause stable diffusion very hard to understand for example the upside down pose is a very difficult one. You may need more experiment with poses that could be rare in the data base.

items.name: Frida Gustavsson
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Frida Gustavsson is a Swedish actress and model, mainly known for her role as Freydis in the TV show Vikings: Valhalla.

1020-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (fr1d4gus:0.99), a woman as a movie star, freckles, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: BikeMaker
items.description:
SDXL (1024x1024) note: Use also negative weights, check examples. Choose versions from the menu on top.


BikeMaker is a tool for generating all types of—you guessed it—bikes. It was trained on an in-house developed dataset of 180 designs with interesting concept features. The model either fixes the input or makes it more interesting for variations.

Use Hires. fix (4x_RealisticRescaler, 4x-Ultrasharp upscalers with denoising strength around 0.3-0.6) for best details in txt2img!

You can combine it with my (or any other) models for added (sur)realism. Check the gallery for examples.

Experiment with weights around 0.1-1 (lower values will tend to create a modern bike or electro bike, higher sci-fi motorbikes), CLIP SKIP 1-2 (2 works better for some stylized models). The model works with a bike token (try to use a combination bike|scooter, vehicle|bike, and so on). It will also style a combined vehicle.

LyCORIS/LoHA experiment trained 768x768, NR 32 + NA 16 dimensions. I am not aiming for technical realism with this series, the models are more focused on design ideas. If you want to learn more about AI-augmented design and algorithmic art, check my web pages.

For my notes on training and use of stable diffusion models, check https://sandner.art/articles/ai/

If you can afford it, support my work by buying me a coffee to keep those costly render cores go: https://ko-fi.com/airesearch

Have fun rendering!

items.name: Alex Gross Style
items.description:
Alex Gross is an American contemporary artist known for his thought-provoking and visually captivating paintings.

His style can be described as a fusion of realism, pop art, and surrealism. Gross often combines elements from different eras and cultures, creating juxtapositions that challenge traditional notions of identity and consumerism.

Gross's artwork frequently incorporates themes of popular culture, nostalgia, and social commentary. He explores the impact of mass media, advertising, and consumerism on society, often presenting his subjects with a touch of irony and introspection.

His paintings are characterized by their meticulous attention to detail and the use of vibrant colors. Gross often incorporates intricate patterns, intricate textures, and richly layered compositions, creating visually compelling and complex narratives.

Through his art, Gross encourages viewers to question the status quo and reflect on the complexities of contemporary society. He invites viewers to delve beneath the surface and explore the underlying emotions and stories within his intricately constructed worlds.

Alex Gross's artwork has been exhibited internationally and is widely collected. His unique blend of realism and surrealism, combined with his incisive social commentary, continues to engage and captivate audiences.

items.name: Ando Fuchs Style
items.description:
Ando Fuchs, hailing from San Candido, South Tyrol, Italy, is a self-taught photographer primarily focused on capturing the interactions between urban spaces and passersby.

He is known for capturing moments when his subjects are utterly natural, striving to make viewers "feel" the image - the core aim of his photography.

Raised in a foster family after losing his parents at an early age, Fuchs discovered his passion for photography in the mid-1980s.

After gaining diverse professional experience in the hotel and construction businesses, he returned to his passion in 2009 and has never left home without a camera since.

Although he generally shoots with a digital camera, he occasionally uses film.

Describing himself as a person who constantly doubts himself and his work, Fuchs is never satisfied with the results.

He finds difficulty in accepting praise, questioning its sincerity, but considers this trait as the driving force of his growth.

Fuchs, who has never attended any photography seminars and honed all his skills through practice, now lives and works in Zilliane, Austria, close to the Italian border.

He places the mood and imagery of a frame above technical perfection and often says, "Don't ask me about the camera and lens I used to take a picture, tell me what the image says to you."
